- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is motivated by questions in theoretical distributed computing and provides a solution to a problem in the immediate snapshot wait-free model.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper develops the combinatorial theory of abstract simplex path subdivisions.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper deals with symmetry breaking, which is a common topic in game theory.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with distributed computing, which often involves communication and coordination among nodes in a network.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may involve analyzing the complexity of the solution provided for the weak symmetry breaking task.
